headline: Nvidia earnings, Trump rally, Fed spending: Market Takeaways
summary: Today on Asking for a Trend, Host Josh Lipton dives into the latest stock market moves (^DJI, ^IXIC, ^GSPC) and the geopolitical impact of the Russia-Ukraine conflict.Yahoo Finance Markets & Data Editor Jared Blikre breaks down the market rally driven by Trump's presidential win, growing anticipation for Nvidia's (NVDA) upcoming earnings report, and bitcoin's (BTC-USD) record surge. President-elect Trump has named Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy to lead the proposed Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), aimed at reducing federal spending. Former Clinton administration official Elaine Kamarck warns that while spending cuts are necessary, they must be realistic and well-detailed. Finally, let’s look ahead to tomorrow, Wednesday, November 20. In addition to Nvidia, TJX Companies (TJX), Palo Alto Networks (PANW), and Target (TGT) will also release their third quarter earnings results.This post was written by Cindy Mizaku.

headline: Nvidia Q3 earnings, Fed commentary: What to Watch
summary: Asking for a Trend anchor Josh Lipton details the key events investors will be watching tomorrow, Wednesday, November 20. Nvidia (NVDA) takes the spotlight as it prepares to release its third quarter earnings results, with market participants eager to see if the company can maintain its growth trajectory. Other notable companies reporting include TJX Companies (TJX), Palo Alto Networks (PANW), Target (TGT), Snowflake (SNOW), Williams-Sonoma (WSM), and NIO (NIO). Meanwhile, the financial world will hear commentary from Federal Reserve governors Lisa Cook, Michelle Bowman, and Boston Fed President Susan Collins. Their speeches will provide insights into the central bank's monetary policy and economic outlooks. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend here. This post was written by Angel Smith
